config FREETZ_PACKAGE_PYTHON3_CRYPTOGRAPHY
	bool "cryptography 43.0.3 (UNSUPPORTED on MIPS - use PyCryptodome)"
	depends on FREETZ_PACKAGE_PYTHON3
	depends on FREETZ_SHOW_DEVELOPER
	select FREETZ_PACKAGE_PYTHON3_CFFI
	select FREETZ_LIB_libcrypto if !FREETZ_PACKAGE_OPENSSL
	select FREETZ_LIB_libssl if !FREETZ_PACKAGE_OPENSSL
	default n
	help
		*** WARNING: NOT SUPPORTED ON MIPS ARCHITECTURE ***
		
		cryptography requires Rust compiler for building.
		Rust removed MIPS support in version 1.72+ (year 2023).
		
		THIS PACKAGE WILL FAIL TO BUILD ON MIPS DEVICES.
		
		ALTERNATIVE: Use python3-pycryptodome instead!
		PyCryptodome provides the same cryptographic functionality
		(AES, RSA, SHA, SSL/TLS) without requiring Rust.
		
		See PYTHON3_CRYPTOGRAPHY_UNSUPPORTED.md for migration guide.
		
		---
		
		cryptography is a package which provides cryptographic recipes and
		primitives to Python developers.
		
		Features:
		  - SSL/TLS support
		  - X.509 certificate handling
		  - Symmetric encryption (AES, ChaCha20, etc.)
		  - Asymmetric encryption (RSA, ECDSA, etc.)
		  - Message digests and signatures
		  - Key derivation functions
		
		Dependencies:
		  - Python 3.x
		  - cffi (Python C Foreign Function Interface)
		  - OpenSSL >= 1.1.1 (for cryptographic operations)
		  - Rust compiler (build-time only, on host system) ← NOT AVAILABLE FOR MIPS
		
		Build complexity: IMPOSSIBLE on MIPS
		  - Requires Rust compiler with MIPS target (removed from Rust 1.72+)
		  - Will fail with error: "can't find crate for 'core'"
		
		Size: N/A (build will fail)
		
		WWW: https://cryptography.io/
